            <p><choice corresp="#a4"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:carling2000"/><citedRange>72</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:hackstein1995"/><citedRange>79</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:kolver1965"/><citedRange>16, 34, 113</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a5"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... you have been named in the sixteen cities as destroying in relation to the discipline of Śākyamuni ...</seg></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">(Da(?) euer Verhalten(?)) ... in der Lehre des Śakyamuni nachlässig [war], ihr Nonnen, wurdet ihr in 16 Städten Zerstörerinnen genannt.</seg><seg type="sec_transl" resp="TI">((Since(?) your behaviour(?)) ... [was] negligent in the teaching of Śakyamuni, you nuns, in 16 cities you were called the she-destroyers.</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>217, 248</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a6"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:carling2000"/><citedRange>333</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1954"/><citedRange>719</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a7"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:carling2000"/><citedRange>228</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:hackstein1995"/><citedRange>141</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... Why did you not live an eternal life among the humans? ...</seg></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">Ziehet [eure] Zunge aus dem Munde!</seg><seg type="sec_transl" resp="TI">Pull [your] tongue from [your] mouth!</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>325</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a8"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:carling2000"/><citedRange>311</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1957"/><citedRange>206</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1995"/><citedRange>67</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b2"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1957"/><citedRange>285</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... || in the M.-tune: || With our own hand we tear our own tongue out from the mouth ...</seg></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">Eigenhändig ziehen wir die eigene Zunge aus dem Munde [und] (schneiden sie mit) glühenden Me(ssern ab).</seg><seg type="sec_transl" resp="TI">With [our] own hand we pull [our] own tongue out of [our] mouth [and] (cut it off with) red-hot kn(ives).</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>324</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b3"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:hackstein1995"/><citedRange>65</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... we make torture to ourselves to our own tongue, oh compassionate one. 1. ...</seg></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... wir tadelten die in der Zucht Stehenden.</seg><seg type="sec_transl" resp="TI">... we scolded those under the discipline.</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>173</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b4"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:hackstein1995"/><citedRange>100</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>412 n.2</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... we acknowledge our sin [and] remove our delusion ...</seg></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">Wir bekennen unsere Schuld [und] beseitigen unser Vergehen: Möge uns Verzeihung sein ...</seg><seg type="sec_transl" resp="TI">We confess our guilt [and] eliminate our offence: may forgiveness be ours ...</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>416</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice></p>
